Loading Data

stroke = read.csv("healthcare-dataset-stroke-data.csv")

Data Cleaning

stroke = stroke %>% 
  select(-id) %>% 
  mutate(gender = factor(gender, levels = c("Male", "Female")),
         heart_disease = factor(heart_disease),
         work_type = factor(work_type),
         ever_married = factor(ever_married),
         smoking_status = factor(smoking_status),
         hypertension = factor(hypertension),
         Residence_type = factor(Residence_type),
         bmi = as.numeric(bmi),
         stroke = factor(stroke),
         age = as.integer(age)) 
## Warning in mask$eval_all_mutate(quo): NAs introduced by coercion
stroke = na.omit(stroke)
head(stroke)

set.seed(1000)

train %>% 
  ggplot() + 
  ggtitle("Box Plot of Glucose Level for Different Work Types")+

It is easy to see, that the Never_worked people in this data set are all young. Therefore, no one who never worked has a stroke is not because they do not have pressure, it might be just because they are young.

Creating Recipe

stroke_recipe = train %>% 
  recipe(stroke ~ gender+
           age+
           hypertension+
           heart_disease+
           ever_married+
           work_type+
           Residence_type+
           avg_glucose_level+
           bmi+
           smoking_status) %>% 
  step_dummy(all_nominal_predictors()) %>%
  step_center(all_predictors()) %>% 
  step_scale(all_predictors())

Model Selection

Logistic Regression

control <- control_resamples(save_pred = TRUE)
log_reg <- logistic_reg() %>%
  set_engine("glm") %>%
  set_mode("classification")
log_wkflow <- workflow() %>%
  add_model(log_reg) %>%
  add_recipe(stroke_recipe)
log_fit <- fit_resamples(log_wkflow, stroke_folds)
collect_metrics(log_fit)
## # A tibble: 2  6

LDA

lda_mod <- discrim_linear() %>%
  set_mode("classification") %>%
  set_engine("MASS")
lda_wkflow <- workflow() %>%
  add_model(lda_mod) %>%
add_recipe(stroke_recipe)
lda_tune_res <- fit_resamples(resamples = stroke_folds, lda_wkflow, control = control)
collect_metrics(lda_tune_res)

Random Forest

forest_spec = rand_forest() %>% 
  set_engine("ranger", importance = "impurity") %>% 
  set_mode("classification") %>% 
  set_args(mtry = tune(), 
           trees = tune(),
           min_n = tune())
forest_wf = workflow() %>% 
  add_model(forest_spec) %>% 
  add_recipe(stroke_recipe)
param_grid = grid_regular(mtry(range = c(1,10)), 
                          min_n(range = c(5,20)), 
                          trees(range = c(200,1000)),
                          levels = 10)
rf_tune_res <- tune_grid(
  forest_wf,
  resamples = stroke_folds, 
  grid = param_grid, 
  metrics = metric_set(roc_auc)
)
write_rds(rf_tune_res, file = "rf_res.rds")
rf = read_rds("rf_res.rds")
autoplot(rf)

best_rf = rf%>% 
  collect_metrics() %>% 
  arrange(desc(mean)) %>% 
  slice(1)
best_rf
## # A tibble: 1  9
##    mtry trees min_n .metric .estimator  mean     n std_err .config              
##   <int> <int> <int> <chr>   <chr>      <dbl> <int>   <dbl> <chr>                
## 1     1   733    18 roc_auc binary     0.821     5  0.0187 Preprocessor1_Model0
rf_final = finalize_workflow(forest_wf,best_rf)
final_fit = fit(rf_final, data = train)
final_fit %>% 
  extract_fit_engine() %>% 
  vip()

Boosted Tree

boost = boost_tree(trees = tune()) %>% 
  set_engine("xgboost") %>% 
  set_mode("classification")
boost_wf = workflow() %>% 
  add_model(boost) %>% 
  add_recipe(stroke_recipe)

boost_grid = grid_regular(trees(c(10,2000)), levels = 10)
boost_tune_res = tune_grid(
  boost_wf,
  resamples = stroke_folds,
  grid = boost_grid,
  metrics = metric_set(roc_auc)
)
write_rds(boost_tune_res, file = "boost_res.rds")
bst = read_rds("boost_res.rds")
autoplot(bst)

best_boosting = bst%>% 
  collect_metrics() %>% 
  arrange(desc(mean)) %>% 
  slice(1)
best_boosting

Support Vector Machine

svm_linear_spec <- svm_poly(degree = 1) %>%
  set_mode("classification") %>%
  set_engine("kernlab")
svm_linear_wf <- workflow() %>%
  add_model(svm_linear_spec %>% set_args(cost = tune())) %>%
  add_formula(stroke ~ .)
param_grid <- grid_regular(cost(), levels = 10)
svm_tune_res <- tune_grid(
  svm_linear_wf, 
  resamples = stroke_folds, 
  grid = param_grid
)
write_rds(svm_tune_res, file = "svm_res.rds")
svm = read_rds("svm_res.rds")
autoplot(svm)

best_svm = svm%>% 
  collect_metrics() %>% 
  arrange(desc(mean)) %>% 
  slice(1)
best_svm

Neural Network

library(nnet)
nn_wf = workflow() %>% 
  add_model(nnet_fit) %>% 
  add_recipe(stroke_recipe)
stroke_recipe_2 = train %>% 
  recipe(stroke ~ gender+
           age+
           hypertension+
           heart_disease+
           ever_married+
           work_type+
           Residence_type+
           avg_glucose_level+
           bmi+
           smoking_status) %>% 
  step_dummy(all_nominal_predictors()) %>%
  step_center(all_predictors()) %>% 
  step_scale(all_predictors()) %>% 
  prep(training = train, retain = TRUE)
train_normalized <- bake(stroke_recipe_2, new_data = train, all_predictors())
nnet_fit <-
  mlp(epochs = 10, hidden_units = 5, dropout = 0.1) %>%
  set_mode("classification") %>% 
  set_engine("nnet", verbose = 0) %>% 
  fit(stroke ~ ., data = bake(stroke_recipe_2, new_data = NULL))
nnet_fit
nn_res<- predict(train, nnet_fit)
